Job Description

Patrick Capital Markets works with a broad range of investment banking clients that seek to raise capital in private placement debt and equity transactions in a wide variety of offering structures (1031 exchanges, limited partnership, etc.) and industry sectors. We are expanding our compliance team and looking for candidates that can accomplish the following:

 Develop a positive and supportive rapport with registered representatives and understand their securities practice;
 Work with our registered representatives on transactions to coordinate an offering and marketing plan that is compliant with regulatory standards;
 Conduct compliance tasks such as audits, email review, activities acknowledgements, outside business activity review, state registrations monitoring;
 Assess risk factors and review suitability of investors and approve or decline their participation in a private placement based on reasonable assessment of their subscription documents;
 Interact professionally with offering sponsors and their investors;
 Review and assess changing regulatory guidance and apply it to our specific business model. 

Requirements for the Position:

FINRA Series 7 and Series 24 licenses;
Compliance experience at a broker-dealer preferred;
Team player and self-starter with the ability to manage time, juggle projects, work efficiently, and make reasoned judgments;
Excellent communication, writing and interpersonal skills;
Knowledge of Excel, DocuSign, SmartSheet, and Word, considered a plus. 

Company Description

Patrick Capital Markets is an independent broker-dealer based in St. Louis, MO. Through our network of independent registered representatives, our focus is investment banking, wholesaling, third party marketing and alternative investments – primarily to institutions, RIAs, and accredited investors. We work closely with, and share offices with our affiliate firm, Saxony Securities, Inc., which serves as a traditional retail brokerage firm for its independent representatives.

We are a small firm that offers employees a collaborative and flexible work environment, and an opportunity to grow with us.This position offers the potential to advance within our group of companies.

