Position Summary

The Compliance Analyst supports the compliance team by creating, maintaining, and analyzing reports that confirm compliance with client guidelines as well as federal and state securities rules and laws. The Compliance Analyst will focus on trade surveillance including trade execution and allocation, investigation of exceptions, producing reports, completion of certifications and questionnaires and will increase responsibilities over time.

Preferred Qualifications And Skills

Bachelor's degree in a field requiring strong analytical and quantitative skills;

Knowledge of equity investments and investment adviser rules and regulations;
Experience with or the ability to learn Charles River batch compliance and post trade alert reviews;
Experience working with and analyzing financial data from a variety of data sources; 
Excellent communication skills;
The ability to work independently and with other members of the Compliance Team as well as collaborate with other internal business partners;
Proficient in Excel;
Ability to obtain a working knowledge of internal processing systems; and
Possess a willingness to continually increase her/his knowledge of the financial services industry and compliance rules, regulations and best practices.

Kennedy Capital Management, Inc. is an equal Opportunity Employer.
